NAME
       umount - unmount filesystems

USAGE
       umount device

DESCRIPTION
       This manual documents the UZIX version of umount.It's been
       significantly  shortened,   but	not  many  features  have
       actually been removed. However, there may  be  differences
       from the GNU version.

       Umount will unmount a filesystem (device) from your  local
       filesystem that was previously mounted with mount.

EXAMPLES
       For example, I might umount the directory /floppy,that was
       mounted from /dev/fd0. To do it, I just need to command:
	  umount /floppy

